value.title: Russians ‘Have Committed’ to Not Interfering in Elections, Trump Aide Insists
value.excerpt: Robert C. O’Brien, the national security adviser, said he warned his Russian counterpart there would be “no tolerance” for interference, but didn’t mention evidence of Moscow’s influence operations.

value.title: Will new Florida voters tip the election in favor of Joe Biden?
value.excerpt: Are we there yet? After the first debate, and the news about Donald Trump, many Americans are wondering when the election will end.

value.title: Donald Trump Jr. Among Names Floated for Open Pennsylvania Senate Seat [REPORT]
value.excerpt: Media reports are conflicting about whether or not Donald Trump Jr.'s name is being considered for a 2022 Pennsylvania run.

value.title: Trump's infection shows officials must take virus seriously - Germany's Altmaier
value.excerpt: German Economy Minister Peter Altmaier said on Sunday that U.S. President Donald Trump's coronavirus infection showed that politicians must take the COVID-19 pandemic more seriously and stop minimizing its health risks.

value.title: White House gives New Jersey officials list of at least 206 people who attended Trump fundraiser
value.excerpt: The White House has supplied the New Jersey Department of Health with the names of more than 200 individuals who attended a fundraiser last week just hours before President Trump announced that he had contracted COVID-19.

value.title: Pence to maintain 'aggressive schedule' as Trump remains in hospital, campaign adviser says
value.excerpt: A senior Trump campaign adviser said on Sunday that Vice President Mike Pence will maintain “a very full aggressive schedule” while the president is being treated in the hospital for COVID-19.

value.title: VP Pence and second lady test negative for COVID, twice in three days
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and his wife, Karen, have against tested negative again for COVID-19 just days after President Trump and the first lady were diagnosed with the virus, White House officials confirmed to Fox News.

value.title: Senior adviser: Biden to be tested again Sunday
value.excerpt: Symone Sanders, a senior adviser to the Biden campaign, said Sunday the campaign is not concerned about continuing events following President Donald Trump's Covid-19 diagnosis, because it is adhering to health guidelines and testing the former vice president "regularly.

value.title: Dr. Sanjay Gupta: Trump shouldn't be discharged tomorrow
value.excerpt: CNN's Dr. Sanjay Gupta reacts to a presser given by President Trump's medical team in which one of the doctors said Trump might be discharged from Walter Reed medical center as early as tomorrow, despite the fact that the President has had at least two concerning drops in oxygen levels.

value.title: 'This election is about Donald Trump, up or down': Focus group pollsters
value.excerpt: Peter Hart, Democratic Pollster, Hart Research Associates, and Nicole McCleskey, Republican Pollster, Public Opinion Strategies, talk to Chuck Todd about a post-debate focus group they conducted for Meet the Press.

value.title: With Trump hospitalized, VP Mike Pence will visit Arizona for a Thursday rally, campaign says
value.excerpt: Pence will host a rally at a tactical-gear supply business in Peoria. His visit had been expected for weeks, but COVID-19 has since rocked the campaign.

value.title: Jim Carrey Plays Joe Biden in ‘S.N.L.’ Season Premiere
value.excerpt: Chris Rock hosted the first live episode since “S.N.L.” was driven from its studio by the coronavirus, and the show didn’t hold back on jokes about President Trump’s diagnosis.

value.title: Trump said to be improving but next 48 hours 'critical'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump says in a video from his hospital quarters that he is feeling better as he battles the novel coronavirus and hopes to “be back soon.”

value.title: ‘SNL’ Kicks Off New Season With POTUS Debate AKA Alec Baldwin’s Trump & Jim Carrey’s Biden Go “Off The Rails.”

value.title: 'The Squad' Responds to Twitter Policy Banning Posts Wishing for Trump's Death: 'Excuse Me?'
value.excerpt: "So... you mean to tell us you could've done this the whole time?" Congresswoman Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez tweeted.

value.title: READ: Trump's physician says the President is 'not out of the woods' but his team is 'cautiously optimistic'
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump remains hospitalized at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center after testing positive for Covid-19.

value.title: Supporters gather for Prayer vigil for Trump outside Walter Reed
value.excerpt: President Trump supporters lined up in front of Walter Reed Hospital Saturday evening, to show support for Trump who was recently diagnosed with coronavirus.

value.title: Trump family, aides flouted Cleveland hotel mask mandate ahead of debate
value.excerpt: Hours before they were seen watching Tuesday's presidential debate without masks in violation of safety protocols, members of President Donald Trump's family, campaign staff and White House team also flouted a mask mandate at a hotel frequented by visitors to Cleveland Clinic.

value.title: Joe Biden says it's 'appalling' not to wear a mask on public transit
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden touted mask-wearing as a form of patriotism on Saturday, criticizing the administration for not doing more to advance the practice during the coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Advisers made last-minute push to get reluctant Trump to Walter Reed
value.excerpt: Marine One was idling on the South Lawn Friday as President Donald Trump's advisers were inside the White House making a last-minute push to get him to board the helicopter.

value.title: Was Trump ever on oxygen? Health, security experts say America needs 'total honesty' on president's condition
value.excerpt: Dr. Sean Conley created confusion about President Trump's COVID-19 diagnosis, which national security and health experts say is unnecessary.

value.title: Doctors say giving Trump the antiviral drug remdesivir is a sign his infection may be serious — even though the timeline is still unclear
value.excerpt: Trump received an IV infusion of the antiviral drug remdesivir on Friday. The therapy is typically reserved for severe cases.

value.title: Michael Cohen responds to Trump’s positive COVID-19 test: 'This was all preventable'
value.excerpt: President Trump’s former attorney Michael Cohen blasted the chief executive’s COVID-19 diagnosis Friday, claiming that the White House is to blame.

value.title: Bernie Sanders wishes Trump and First Lady 'full and speedy recovery'
value.excerpt: Sen. Bernie Sanders, I-Vt., on Saturday wished President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump a “full and speedy recovery’ from COVID-19, after they were diagnosed with the virus earlier this week.

value.title: Trump took photos, had roundtable with donors at Bedminster fundraiser hours before announcing Covid diagnosis
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump's big-dollar fundraiser at his New Jersey golf club went on as planned Thursday night despite the President and staff knowing he had been exposed to coronavirus.
